name: Vanessa Shealy
tweet: I think we have an important job as parents to see only the best in our children. It's someone else's job to see the shortcomings. So I don't regret those years of not knowing. I was able to enjoy them in a way that I might not have if an autism "label" had already been applied.

tweet: Everyone was so taken by his happiness, his eye contact, and above all, his emerging WORDS that I received a lot of reassurance that he was ‚Äúfine‚Äù and just ‚Äúspirited.‚Äù I welcomed this reassurance.

tweet: He would run alongside a wall, or the couch, and look at the blurry movement of the world out of the corners of his eyes. I mentioned this to a lot of people - friends, family, even his pediatrician. No one suspected #autism...
